Binary packing for a given input

Run time:
O(n) because we have to go thorugh the whole tree at least once 
to get all the packing done
but actually it is O(2n)

Space complexity:
O(log n), given that number of nodes is n, because of the height of the tree

$ proj3 flr/r2_flr.txt output
Width: 3.411589e+06
Height: 4.923995e+06

X-coordinate: 5.193600e+05
Y-coordinate: 0.000000e+00

Elapsed time: 0.000000e+00

